<subSubSection id="4012E3D6F8B8F3C062137694426B0692" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F50801A959F89B042715ABB4E6A01394" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F35F2A5CF6B7BE0E8047B60C4BE60B79" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
Adapted from 
<bibRefCitation id="AA984DC6BA168EFDDBD6CA0062E29ABC" author="Matsumoto, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 408" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" refId="B37" refString="Matsumoto, H, 1917. A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification. Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo 38: 1 - 408, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" title="A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" volume="38" year="1917">Matsumoto (1917)</bibRefCitation>
, H. L. 
<bibRefCitation id="167BA569B11E4D15A5AADF9EA031247E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" author="Clark, HL" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 302" refId="B8" refString="Clark, HL, 1911. North Pacific Ophiurans in the collection of the United States National Museum. Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin 75: 1 - 302, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" title="North Pacific Ophiurans in the collection of the United States National Museum." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" volume="75" year="1911">Clark (1911)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3D272759AB767CA2EE21E8E4A7A23057" author="Lyman, T" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/31068674page/27/mode/1up" refId="B31" refString="Lyman, T, 1879. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/31068674page/27/mode/1up" url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/31068674page/27/mode/1up" year="1879">Lyman (1879)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F486B16844648A308A58F2545CB57CBD" author="Paterson, GLJ" journalOrPublisher="Historical Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 162" publicationUrl="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" refId="B47" refString="Paterson, GLJ, 1985. The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Historical Series 49: 1 - 162, http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" title="The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." url="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" volume="49" year="1985">Paterson (1985)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="1A49D71CF96E1C8503EBFE62B95F9C4A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.11682" author="Koehler, R" journalOrPublisher="Annales des Sciences Naturelles Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" refId="B21" refString="Koehler, R, 1904. Ophiures de l'expedition du Siboga. Part 1. Ophiures de mer profonde. Weber, Siboga Expeditie. MEJ Brill, Leiden 45a: 1-176. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.11682" title="Ophiures de l'expedition du Siboga. Part 1. Ophiures de mer profonde. Weber, Siboga Expeditie. MEJ Brill, Leiden 45 a: 1 - 176." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.11682" year="1904">Koehler (1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C9154B32852FB0DCC15E1EA9314EA0C0" author="Koehler, R" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 480" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" refId="B22" refString="Koehler, R, 1922. Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 5: 1 - 480, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" title="Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" volume="5" year="1922">1922</bibRefCitation>
). Disc rounded to sub-pentagonal, and covered by irregular overlapping disc scales with sparse to coarse minute granules. Radial shields ovoid, naked, and widely separated by disc scales with granules. Three or four spiniform lateral oral papillae, with one ventralmost tooth at jaw apex. Dorsal arm plates contiguous at arm base then separated. Ventral arm plates pentagonal to tetragonal, and separated. Four to seven arm spines at each lateral arm plate. Arm spines smooth to rugose, one to three arm segments in length, thick, with blunt tip. Mostly single, large, flat, oval tentacle scale.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1C9973B22E473D380B85080E35223A96" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C5A4D5D41B707CE2F7B021239E60E05C" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0672AD3007233B6DC96BD47E6A030557" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
100-2194 m depth, North Pacific, Australia, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea, South Africa. Substrate of mud, fine grey sand, 
<taxonomicName id="AED0300CDE556ABA120EC2D82D082311" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subPhylum" subPhylum="Foraminifera">Foraminifera</taxonomicName>
, and small stones (
<bibRefCitation id="66364A544E0F2338CEDCC0D34E5CD7F0" author="Olbers, JM" journalOrPublisher="Abc Taxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 354" publicationUrl="http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" refId="B46" refString="Olbers, JM, Griffiths, CL, O'Hara, TD, Samyn, Y, 2019. Field guide to the brittle and basket stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) of South Africa. Abc Taxa 19: 1 - 354, http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" title="Field guide to the brittle and basket stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) of South Africa." url="http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" volume="19" year="2019">Olbers et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6D8CAD4EFF66332B42CB936737EC5D46" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F60BAEA548686B82D0EF9B60CEC5EA07" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3378E2B13F09BAE5948DBC801526B765" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicName id="BC1D237D23418D2F93EBC640F7FA75F5" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F36BAAD055313240384F0E3F0A61E24A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was created by 
<bibRefCitation id="9555C35589747F823CF82C8DFBBD181F" author="Matsumoto, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 408" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" refId="B37" refString="Matsumoto, H, 1917. A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification. Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo 38: 1 - 408, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" title="A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" volume="38" year="1917">Matsumoto (1917)</bibRefCitation>
for species, which at the time were included in the genera 
<taxonomicName id="BA43EA41AA30AF75EA3A5629A210DD74" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1869" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiomitra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomitra" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D672ADE530D9E95507498C6C1C5B50E6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiomitra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DFBC3F697D760574FFC8052B4B6DDE5C" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiomitrella" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomitrella" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5E76A624C15A87444D9D87E2996C460E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiomitrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="A1302D9AE1D132F8858706C9E2D03FE5" authorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1842" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiacantha" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiacantha" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="825ADD3984D0F2F7DD12612F0212C29D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="9BF219A0CC0D29CE800051C82D30EF2B" author="Paterson, GLJ" journalOrPublisher="Historical Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 162" publicationUrl="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" refId="B47" refString="Paterson, GLJ, 1985. The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Historical Series 49: 1 - 162, http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" title="The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." url="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" volume="49" year="1985">Paterson (1985)</bibRefCitation>
noted that the ophiuroid genus 
<taxonomicName id="1E23F9780445E0C2D29BB59A14770120" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="95640E53CF449C7D2474277E25346994" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior homonym of a reptilian genus described by 
<bibRefCitation id="E9829B8DAA97B9AE3DADAC854E05EFAC" author="Fitzinger, L" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" refId="B12" refString="Fitzinger, L, 1843. Systema Reptilium. In: Fasciculus primus: Amblyglossae. Vindobonae: Braumueller und Seidel, 106." title="Systema Reptilium. In: Fasciculus primus: Amblyglossae. Vindobonae: Braumueller und Seidel, 106." year="1843">Fitzinger (1843)</bibRefCitation>
. Some later works (
<bibRefCitation id="A8CA9E2DC60399D1143910126003454F" author="Olbers, JM" journalOrPublisher="Abc Taxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 354" publicationUrl="http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" refId="B46" refString="Olbers, JM, Griffiths, CL, O'Hara, TD, Samyn, Y, 2019. Field guide to the brittle and basket stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) of South Africa. Abc Taxa 19: 1 - 354, http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" title="Field guide to the brittle and basket stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) of South Africa." url="http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" volume="19" year="2019">Olbers et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8F4C96048B8DA22F0344D61B3599473A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.6620/ZS.2021.60-59" author="Okanishi, M" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Studies (Taipei, Taiwan)" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 13" refId="B45" refString="Okanishi, M, Matsuo, T, Fujita, T, 2021. A new species of the genus Ophiomonas Djakonov (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea: Amphilepididae) from the deep-sea of Japan. Zoological Studies (Taipei, Taiwan) 60: 1 - 13, DOI: https://doi.org/10.6620/ZS.2021.60-59" title="A new species of the genus Ophiomonas Djakonov (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea: Amphilepididae) from the deep-sea of Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.6620/ZS.2021.60-59" volume="60" year="2021">Okanishi et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
) used the name 
<taxonomicName id="F0C99F3669A00D8A004A25237DE995EF" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3BE247C1DC4048040D469FF554F2A5C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in quotation marks, indicating its invalid status, while other works (Suppl. material 1) seem to have been oblivious to the issue, causing confusion and taxonomic instability. Article 23.9.1 of the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (
<bibRefCitation id="400C344AE4086348951D99E47FD2D7E0" author="International Commission of Nomenclature" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Ecology Resources" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" refId="B16" refString="International Commission of Nomenclature, 2000. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4th edn. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature 1999, London." title="International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th edn. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature 1999, London." year="2000">International Commission of Nomenclature 2000</bibRefCitation>
), states that &quot;prevailing usage of a name must be maintained when the senior homonym has been used as a 
<normalizedToken id="11E41CC32539340D6B8AAACFBA096736" originalValue="taxon’s">taxon's</normalizedToken>
presumed valid name, in at least 25 works, published by at least ten authors in the immediately preceding 50 years and encompassing a span of not less than ten years&quot;. In the present case, the 50-year period extends from 1971 to 2021 and 25 publications by more than ten authors have been found in this period (Suppl. material 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7580967C4F426DE092BFAED31D0F85A" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
Both names are available, because they have been published with either a description or mention of a type species, and they satisfy articles 10, 11, and 12 of the Code. 
<bibRefCitation id="F5EE5EF5F7E59BA0229969D8F51FA95A" author="Fitzinger, L" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" refId="B12" refString="Fitzinger, L, 1843. Systema Reptilium. In: Fasciculus primus: Amblyglossae. Vindobonae: Braumueller und Seidel, 106." title="Systema Reptilium. In: Fasciculus primus: Amblyglossae. Vindobonae: Braumueller und Seidel, 106." year="1843">Fitzinger (1843)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the 
<normalizedToken id="0BE6BCE0F30B82128437DFEB3073B783" originalValue="reptile’s">reptile's</normalizedToken>
name 
<taxonomicName id="7231AB5F58B602A22099B5BF2BDDC81E" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="859C49187DD523D9D649E4F804F6843C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="D9ADC35ACD7300B7FA31256C3E618432" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1835" class="Reptilia" family="Pygopodidae" genus="Lialis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lialis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3AE89F2B1D2E5B2412E92F1CFF48ACAD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Lialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gray, 1834 with the same type species 
<taxonomicName id="480F8D079EEFB5D25A42F88F8F9816B7" genus="L." lsidName="L. burtonis" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="burtonis">
<emphasis id="3BB5B54F6E6456B17D696161B30FEA4C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">L. burtonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gray, 1835, immediately making 
<taxonomicName id="41A02646B9DCAA81808FFAD97A14CC03" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1940A9EC6BC9617674F2E3B8FD212D1A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fitzinger, 1843 a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="733FCE5811405C19F7AAE9609FA83AE9" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1835" class="Reptilia" family="Pygopodidae" genus="Lialis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lialis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C94F5D3C208153E0250CACB47C3A42BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Lialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="577C2A2EAE3CCFEAFD09C46A0EFAE499" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5067.3.1" author="Shea, GM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="301 - 351" refId="B48" refString="Shea, GM, 2021. Nomenclature of supra-generic units within the Family Scincidae (Squamata). Zootaxa 5067 (3): 301 - 351, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5067.3.1" title="Nomenclature of supra-generic units within the Family Scincidae (Squamata)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5067.3.1" volume="5067" year="2021">Shea 2021</bibRefCitation>
). 
<normalizedToken id="7074D8BF14DF1C898AF4805CC6692880" originalValue="Fitzinger’s">Fitzinger's</normalizedToken>
contemporary colleagues and later researchers rejected his proposed name change, and 
<taxonomicName id="C8A24333E4E4289FDB3752B7BD81375B" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7C0BBB19131C13A5B4CD1729EAA2AB55" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was thus never used for a reptile and cannot be used in the future, because it lacks a type species separate from 
<taxonomicName id="480201BA84E7715B71698E0B64B58556" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1835" class="Reptilia" family="Pygopodidae" genus="Lialis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lialis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="27E7EC998BB0B13B3C6A004D90CB441A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Lialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Instead, prevailing usage of the name 
<taxonomicName id="7181AEF2E00C66B6159E040E05B4E665" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B60296E14335077C4F020846889D22B4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Matsumoto, 1917 has been shown here and it must be maintained.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9B6B40B9B438AAE6E2A28228A0666EE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicName id="F77EDE3AA280A81E4EBB6FF858FE8889" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8380399DAB137099B3AD2AF99F1060BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to one of the largest and diverse ophiuroid families, 
<taxonomicName id="1CADEC278B412C2164C8CD1C71E6FADF" authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1867" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Ophiacanthidae</taxonomicName>
in the order 
<taxonomicName id="9E559B63916FDEB6DB5E3C65E53C41A3" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="order">Ophiacanthida</taxonomicName>
, and is delineated from most other genera by having minute granular coverage of the disc, smooth and somewhat finely serrated arm spines, ovoid radial shields, and by characters of the arm plates (
<bibRefCitation id="7C9BA3901EDCA5D68523D7BAF6927D0F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.11682" author="Koehler, R" journalOrPublisher="Annales des Sciences Naturelles Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" refId="B21" refString="Koehler, R, 1904. Ophiures de l'expedition du Siboga. Part 1. Ophiures de mer profonde. Weber, Siboga Expeditie. MEJ Brill, Leiden 45a: 1-176. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.11682" title="Ophiures de l'expedition du Siboga. Part 1. Ophiures de mer profonde. Weber, Siboga Expeditie. MEJ Brill, Leiden 45 a: 1 - 176." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.11682" year="1904">Koehler 1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="D27554BFFF8DA0674E3CD131809453F9" author="Koehler, R" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 480" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" refId="B22" refString="Koehler, R, 1922. Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 5: 1 - 480, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" title="Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" volume="5" year="1922">1922</bibRefCitation>
; H. L. 
<bibRefCitation id="B68A0F51C34CAE15CA150BE6F8C386CC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" author="Clark, HL" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 302" refId="B8" refString="Clark, HL, 1911. North Pacific Ophiurans in the collection of the United States National Museum. Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin 75: 1 - 302, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" title="North Pacific Ophiurans in the collection of the United States National Museum." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" volume="75" year="1911">Clark 1911</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1107C92B64D2B25988A256E9C8143EBC" author="Matsumoto, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 408" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" refId="B37" refString="Matsumoto, H, 1917. A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification. Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo 38: 1 - 408, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" title="A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" volume="38" year="1917">Matsumoto 1917</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D2DDCB224B64B0624ED23D4874DD545E" author="Paterson, GLJ" journalOrPublisher="Historical Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 162" publicationUrl="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" refId="B47" refString="Paterson, GLJ, 1985. The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Historical Series 49: 1 - 162, http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" title="The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." url="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" volume="49" year="1985">Paterson 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="028A27F43667610F0D7BA3B18E4F3C03" author="Liao, Y" journalOrPublisher="Zoology of China Invertebrates" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 305" refId="B26" refString="Liao, Y, 2004. Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea. Fauna Sinica. Zoology of China Invertebrates 40: 1 - 305" title="Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea. Fauna Sinica." volume="40" year="2004">Liao 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="747CE7DDAC6C4DF62EC936631F211013" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0139463" author="Martynov, AV" journalOrPublisher="Balkema, Rotterdam" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" refId="B36" refString="Martynov, AV, Ishida, Y, Irimura, S, Tajiri, R, O'Hara, T, Fujita, T, 2015. When ontogeny matters: A new Japanese species of brittle star illustrates the importance of considering both adult and juvenile characters in taxonomic practice. PLoS ONE 10(10): e0139463. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0139463" title="When ontogeny matters: A new Japanese species of brittle star illustrates the importance of considering both adult and juvenile characters in taxonomic practice. PLoS ONE 10 (10): e 0139463." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0139463" year="2015">Martynov et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="17D782DE4C7FB070A5BF9FB2D9F3D35B" author="Olbers, JM" journalOrPublisher="Abc Taxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 354" publicationUrl="http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" refId="B46" refString="Olbers, JM, Griffiths, CL, O'Hara, TD, Samyn, Y, 2019. Field guide to the brittle and basket stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) of South Africa. Abc Taxa 19: 1 - 354, http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" title="Field guide to the brittle and basket stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) of South Africa." url="http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" volume="19" year="2019">Olbers et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, 
<taxonomicName id="08192550438A0898987F5555B8AED7F3" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4FB6C1E1A1E39B946E63A1574713917C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes four species: 
<taxonomicName id="27518C27CD7371F847BC405FFC519D55" genus="O." lsidName="O. cataleimmoidus" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="cataleimmoidus">
<emphasis id="F26E7A509EEF62D5E26080EEA8451930" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">O. cataleimmoidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EA08E729AD950D2B490879647E820084" genus="O." lsidName="O. hylacanthus" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="hylacanthus">
<emphasis id="34CDFD1E609D883DA2F4C9AADDDE7B1B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">O. hylacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C9B14577A58BBB32FA9FD098BD5ACBC3" genus="O." lsidName="O. normani" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="normani">
<emphasis id="E9E682443DF435D42D63EB1FF11F2BE3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">O. normani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5347FA0B5F4C44BF3EAFE5E4A2160" genus="O." lsidName="O. relictus" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="relictus">
<emphasis id="AEA42969066D9D4E2ABBEA16F6B6FB72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">O. relictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="E94DAB0B4BE6A4A29D730308F1815FAA" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1869" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiomitra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomitra" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="19F60315BCA843FE45DAA9495955ACFF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiomitra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="F1DBA1FCBB862AE167170CC4F66C4E43" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3998BFC6BECBDBCA8C72FA9C160E7FC7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having ovoid, separated radial shields, and smooth, long arm spines, but differs in a thorny tip on granules or stumps, 10-16 oral papillae at the jaw, up to nine arm spines (
<bibRefCitation id="399E469C10A82111E3941037D261C9B1" author="Lyman, T" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="309 - 354" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/6587804" refId="B29" refString="Lyman, T, 1869. Preliminary report on the Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae dredged in deep water between Cuba and Florida Reef. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 1: 309 - 354, https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/6587804" title="Preliminary report on the Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae dredged in deep water between Cuba and Florida Reef." url="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/6587804" volume="1" year="1869">Lyman 1869</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7629862C26C2C01EFB27BF92E7C4DAE2" author="Luetken, CF" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="97 - 208" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/28891692" refId="B28" refString="Luetken, CF, Mortensen, T, 1899. Reports on an exploration off the west coasts of Mexico, Central and Southern America and off the Galapagos Islands. XXV. The Ophiuridae. Memoirs of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 23: 97 - 208, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/28891692" title="Reports on an exploration off the west coasts of Mexico, Central and Southern America and off the Galapagos Islands. XXV. The Ophiuridae." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/28891692" volume="23" year="1899">
<normalizedToken id="0E34C1DCD1F15DCBC8129430EE66A94B" originalValue="Lütken">Luetken</normalizedToken>
and Mortensen 1899
</bibRefCitation>
; H. L. 
<bibRefCitation id="AD68753D704367B60CEB764A1FE20FAA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" author="Clark, HL" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 302" refId="B8" refString="Clark, HL, 1911. North Pacific Ophiurans in the collection of the United States National Museum. Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin 75: 1 - 302, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" title="North Pacific Ophiurans in the collection of the United States National Museum." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" volume="75" year="1911">Clark 1911</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4E5B4ED1F814EF585E480BDDA5F9A14F" author="Matsumoto, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 408" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" refId="B37" refString="Matsumoto, H, 1917. A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification. Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo 38: 1 - 408, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" title="A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" volume="38" year="1917">Matsumoto 1917</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="18E0DA9BC1F6840C5ACEE07D33579BE8" author="Koehler, R" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 480" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" refId="B22" refString="Koehler, R, 1922. Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 5: 1 - 480, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" title="Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" volume="5" year="1922">Koehler 1922</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2E544544AD508C72438BD0DC286BFFDA" author="Olbers, JM" journalOrPublisher="Abc Taxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 354" publicationUrl="http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" refId="B46" refString="Olbers, JM, Griffiths, CL, O'Hara, TD, Samyn, Y, 2019. Field guide to the brittle and basket stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) of South Africa. Abc Taxa 19: 1 - 354, http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" title="Field guide to the brittle and basket stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) of South Africa." url="http://www.abctaxa.be/volumes/volume_19_fieldguide-brittle-and-basket-stars" volume="19" year="2019">Olbers et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="C3D46BA22990AF0C419E1AB402D11D88" author="Matsumoto, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 408" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" refId="B37" refString="Matsumoto, H, 1917. A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification. Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Tokyo 38: 1 - 408, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" title="A monograph of Japanese Ophiuroidea, arranged according to a new classification." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7145928page/5/mode/1up" volume="38" year="1917">Matsumoto (1917</bibRefCitation>
b) suggested that contiguous dorsal arm plates on the arm base, and the proximal arm spines not arranged in a fan shape can be used to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="76EBBF81C1AEB9E9F1ABC4C239BF5ADB" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5634F913042F09BC72C41478A007D964" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="B33920EEBC401F27108D829E4AE51F7E" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiomitrella" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomitrella" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="48835FE77BAE4F55ADEEB055F342FA47" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiomitrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas 
<bibRefCitation id="67FBE6BB98AD8A4110C963C8BDFA8B12" author="Koehler, R" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 480" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" refId="B22" refString="Koehler, R, 1922. Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 5: 1 - 480, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" title="Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/77301" volume="5" year="1922">Koehler (1922)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished these from each other by naked radial shields and overlapping disc scales, but 
<bibRefCitation id="540DCDF5B9871CFC48BAF6591CE0D99B" author="Paterson, GLJ" journalOrPublisher="Historical Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 162" publicationUrl="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" refId="B47" refString="Paterson, GLJ, 1985. The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Historical Series 49: 1 - 162, http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" title="The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." url="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2273511" volume="49" year="1985">Paterson (1985)</bibRefCitation>
observed that these characters are not consistent among all species within these genera. However, H. L. 
<bibRefCitation id="59B140AA2FAC555038D4DC79160E7DB3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" author="Clark, HL" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="1 - 302" refId="B8" refString="Clark, HL, 1911. North Pacific Ophiurans in the collection of the United States National Museum. Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin 75: 1 - 302, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" title="North Pacific Ophiurans in the collection of the United States National Museum." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.32556" volume="75" year="1911">Clark (1911)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that 
<taxonomicName id="93562CC8A01FE07C0BFF62664C95CF97" authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1917" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiophthalmus" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4A2AC798BFFE7C1983476C3F5E95D09B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species were remarkably consistent in some specific characters (he examined more than 4,000 specimens). Recent molecular studies suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="9DD331570CB418D171C7ECA653CBEF14" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiomitrella" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomitrella" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5DAC2FFBE06CD4E01A47E66F82936DC6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiomitrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be polyphyletic in the family 
<taxonomicName id="8D656B9D66F54F37D4E8D7D6E7F70F71" authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1867" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Ophiacanthida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Ophiacanthidae</taxonomicName>
, and species from this genus need to be revised (
<bibRefCitation id="D34327982A496558DABD8E2A317AA406" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cub.2019.09.012" author="Christodoulou, M" journalOrPublisher="Current Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="3909 - 3912" refId="B6" refString="Christodoulou, M, O'Hara, TD, Hugall, AF, Arbizu, PM, 2019. Dark Ophiuroid Biodiversity in a Prospective Abyssal Mine Field. Current Biology 29 (22): 3909 - 3912, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cub.2019.09.012" title="Dark Ophiuroid Biodiversity in a Prospective Abyssal Mine Field." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cub.2019.09.012" volume="29" year="2019">Christodoulou et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
